# payment-processing-workflow

The payment processing system implements specialized flows for ACH, credit card and PayPal transactions:

## Payment Method Processing (frontend/src/pages/PaymentGateway.jsx)
Importance Score: 90/100

Key workflows:

1. ACH/Bank Processing
- Routing number validation 
- Default "Pending" status application
- Extended processing time handling

2. Credit Card Processing 
- Specialized validation ruleset
- Immediate success/failure status determination
- Direct payment confirmation

3. PayPal Integration
- Redirect flow simulation
- Return URL handling
- Payment confirmation workflow

## Transaction Status Management (backend/server.js) 
Importance Score: 85/100

Status propagation rules:
- ACH: Initial "Pending" → "Completed"/"Failed" after processing delay
- Credit Card: Immediate "Completed"/"Failed" status
- PayPal: "Pending" during redirect → "Completed" on return

Status updates trigger:
- Stylist record synchronization
- Last payment date tracking
- Rent payment reconciliation

## Method-Specific Validation
Importance Score: 80/100

- ACH: Routing number format and institution verification
- Credit Card: Card number validation, CVV checks, expiration verification
- PayPal: Account linking and authentication validation

